16. ACID Transactions
ACID ensures database reliability. For example, if complaint assignment and audit log insertion happen together, either both should happen or none should happen

ACID:

Atomicity: all or nothing
Consistency: valid state
Isolation: concurrent users don’t corrupt data
Durability: committed data remains saved

